projecttitle: EU recovery programme for floods   component on flood protection and infrastructures
project_descrip: Short: EU RECOVERY PROGRAMME FOR FLOODS   COMPONENT ON FLOOD PROTECTION AND INFRASTRUCTURES Long: reconstruction of embankments, dams and river protection: repairing and upgrading of damaged irrigation and drainage canals: expanding the capacity of pumping stations. This set of infrastructures will increase resilience to flooding in the affected regions of Fier and Vlora in a perspective of climate change adaption. The component may also address infrastructure needs in other regions of the country, which are likely to be exposed to floods emergency.

projecttitle: Kafr El Shekh Wastewater Expansion (KESWE)
project_descrip: Short: KAFR EL SHEKH WASTEWATER EXPANSION (KESWE) Long: The general objective of the project is to improve health standards for residents in Kafr El Shekh Governorate, the quality of irrigation water, as well as the environmental quality of the Nile, Lake Burullus, and the Mediterranean Sea. Investing in wastewater infrastructure will provide first time sanitation services to approximately half a million consumers. Indirect benefits include an expected increase in the volume and quality of fish in Lake Burullus (70% of the country s fishing industry)

projecttitle: Supply and installation of Drip Irrigation Schemes Powered by Photovoltaic in Eritrea
project_descrip: Short: SUPPLY AND INSTALLATION OF DRIP IRRIGATION SCHEMES POWERED BY PHOTOVOLTAIC IN ERITREA Long: The drip irrigaiton schemes powered by photovoltaic contract is for 7 lots covering for  545 ha in 14 sites aiming at increasing production and productivity of subsitence farmers. Through the application of drip irrigation schemes powered by PV the targeted farmers will be enabled to  build their capacity to cultivate their land 2-3 seasons per year. This new agricultural practise will increase production and productivity of the famers, increase their income and thereby  improve their livlihood.

projecttitle: Rehabilitation of Geleb Nursery
project_descrip: Short: REHABILITATION OF GELEB NURSERY Long: The proposed project has as purpose to renovate the nursery at Geleb with its 6 hectares of land serving as centre for applied agricultural research. project_descrip: Short: IMPROVED FOOD SECURITY AND SUSTAINABLE LIVELIHOODS DEVELOPMENT THROUGH INTEGRATED NATURAL RESOURCES MANAGEMENT IN GELEB Long: The project foresees the strengthening of sustainable agriculture through the empowerment of research actors. projecttitle: Adaptation to Climate Change in Jordan
project_descrip: Short: ADAPTATION TO CLIMATE CHANGE IN JORDAN Long: The main objective of the Action is to contribute to the mitigation of climate change risks. The aim is to reduce the vulnerability of farming communities in the Jordan Valley to the impact of climate change through improved supply of irrigation water by increasing the use of reclaimed water in the farms and thus saving valuable freshwater resources that can be used as drinking water in urban areas.     The specific objectives of the Action are:  -to reduce freshwater consumption for irrigation

projecttitle: Construction of Bwanje Valley Dam
project_descrip: Short: CONSTRUCTION OF BWANJE VALLEY DAM Long: The dam will be 40 metres high and approximately 150 m long with a storage capacity of 5.64 million m (resulting in the provision of irrigation water to sufficiently irrigate 800 ha in wet and dry seasons). Works on Bwanje Valley Dam include the construction of a zoned earth-fill dam on a rocky foundation with a right bank spillway allowing flood flows to be safely routed away from the dam into a downstream tributary.
shortdescription: CONSTRUCTION OF BWANJE VALLEY DAM
longdescription: The dam will be 40 metres high and approximately 150 m long with a storage capacity of 5.64 million m (resulting in the provision of irrigation water to sufficiently irrigate 800 ha in wet and dry seasons). Works on Bwanje Valley Dam include the construction of a zoned earth-fill dam on a rocky foundation with a right bank spillway allowing flood flows to be safely routed away from the dam into a downstream tributary.

projecttitle: Wealth creation through Irrigation in the North-Western Province (WIN)
project_descrip: Short: WEALTH CREATION THROUGH IRRIGATION IN THE NORTH-WESTERN PROVINCE (WIN) Long: This proposed Action is designed to reduce the incidence of rural poverty and seeks to contribute to human development by improving the sustainable livelihoods of smallholder farmers in North-Western province (NWP) of Zambia. It will do this by developing their capacity to generate cash incomes by utilising available land and labour during the dry season to engage in high value horticultural production. Increased cash income will give the opportunity for increased social investments such as education and healthcare for children: investments in farming enterprises through purchase of assets (e.g. pumps, ploughs and draught animals) and inputs (fertilisers and improved seed) for rain-fed crop production which allow greater areas to be cultivated with increased yields and hence food insecurity to be reduced: and household investments such as brick walls, tin roofs and generator sets which will improve the quality of life.
shortdescription: WEALTH CREATION THROUGH IRRIGATION IN THE NORTH-WESTERN PROVINCE (WIN)
longdescription: This proposed Action is designed to reduce the incidence of rural poverty and seeks to contribute to human development by improving the sustainable livelihoods of smallholder farmers in North-Western province (NWP) of Zambia.
